Commit
$ git commit -am "ignore files"

Create branch

git branch dev = create branch dev
git chekout dev = move in branch dev
git branch = show branches
git checkout -b add-bootstrap = create new branch add-bootstrap and move in it
git push --set-upstream origin add-bootstarp
$ git push origin dev

Syncing branches
git fetch origin test = Download objects and refs( in the example test) from another repository
git checkout --track origin/test
git checkout -b mybranch origin/abranch =will create mybranch and track origin/abranch
git checkout --track origin/abranch = will only create 'abranch', not a branch with a different name.

Graph the branches on the terminal

git log --graph

